{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":630,"text":"So raise your hand if you know someone"},{"time":3858,"text":"in your immediate family or circle of friends"},{"time":6505,"text":"who suffers from some form of mental illness."},{"time":9993,"text":"Yeah. I thought so. Not surprised."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12777,"text":"And raise your hand if you think that"},{"time":15072,"text":"basic research on fruit flies has anything to do"},{"time":17897,"text":"with understanding mental illness in humans."},{"time":22359,"text":"Yeah. I thought so. I'm also not surprised."},{"time":25152,"text":"I can see I've got my work cut out for me here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28472,"text":"As we heard from Dr. Insel this morning,"},{"time":31060,"text":"psychiatric disorders like autism, depression and schizophrenia"},{"time":35273,"text":"take a terrible toll on human suffering."},{"time":38148,"text":"We know much less about their treatment"},{"time":41361,"text":"and the understanding of their basic mechanisms"},{"time":43967,"text":"than we do about diseases of the body."},{"time":46586,"text":"Think about it: In 2013,"},{"time":49229,"text":"the second decade of the millennium,"},{"time":51184,"text":"if you're concerned about a cancer diagnosis"},{"time":53549,"text":"and you go to your doctor, you get bone scans,"},{"time":56068,"text":"biopsies and blood tests."},{"time":58996,"text":"In 2013, if you're concerned about a depression diagnosis,"},{"time":62861,"text":"you go to your doctor, and what do you get?"},{"time":64824,"text":"A questionnaire."},{"time":66811,"text":"Now, part of the reason for this is that we have"},{"time":69240,"text":"an oversimplified and increasingly outmoded view"},{"time":73063,"text":"of the biological basis of psychiatric disorders."},{"time":76950,"text":"We tend to view them --"},{"time":78193,"text":"and the popular press aids and abets this view --"},{"time":81038,"text":"as chemical imbalances in the brain,"},{"time":84054,"text":"as if the brain were some kind of bag of chemical soup"},{"time":87738,"text":"full of dopamine, serotonin and norepinephrine."},{"time":91938,"text":"This view is conditioned by the fact"},{"time":94265,"text":"that many of the drugs that are prescribed to treat these disorders,"},{"time":97671,"text":"like Prozac, act by globally changing brain chemistry,"},{"time":102342,"text":"as if the brain were indeed a bag of chemical soup."},{"time":106318,"text":"But that can't be the answer,"},{"time":108219,"text":"because these drugs actually don't work all that well."},{"time":111456,"text":"A lot of people won't take them, or stop taking them,"},{"time":114632,"text":"because of their unpleasant side effects."},{"time":117289,"text":"These drugs have so many side effects"},{"time":119349,"text":"because using them to treat a complex psychiatric disorder"},{"time":123305,"text":"is a bit like trying to change your engine oil"},{"time":125994,"text":"by opening a can and pouring it all over the engine block."},{"time":130107,"text":"Some of it will dribble into the right place,"},{"time":132257,"text":"but a lot of it will do more harm than good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135358,"text":"Now, an emerging view"},{"time":137596,"text":"that you also heard about from Dr. Insel this morning,"},{"time":140546,"text":"is that psychiatric disorders are actually"},{"time":143116,"text":"disturbances of neural circuits that mediate"},{"time":146590,"text":"emotion, mood and affect."},{"time":150109,"text":"When we think about cognition,"},{"time":151871,"text":"we analogize the brain to a computer. That's no problem."},{"time":155447,"text":"Well it turns out that the computer analogy"},{"time":158028,"text":"is just as valid for emotion."},{"time":160411,"text":"It's just that we don't tend to think about it that way."},{"time":163197,"text":"But we know much less about the circuit basis"},{"time":166480,"text":"of psychiatric disorders"},{"time":168379,"text":"because of the overwhelming dominance"},{"time":170449,"text":"of this chemical imbalance hypothesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173801,"text":"Now, it's not that chemicals are not important"},{"time":177628,"text":"in psychiatric disorders."},{"time":179165,"text":"It's just that they don't bathe the brain like soup."},{"time":183137,"text":"Rather, they're released in very specific locations"},{"time":186786,"text":"and they act on specific synapses"},{"time":189511,"text":"to change the flow of information in the brain."},{"time":193199,"text":"So if we ever really want to understand"},{"time":195636,"text":"the biological basis of psychiatric disorders,"},{"time":198341,"text":"we need to pinpoint these locations in the brain"},{"time":201373,"text":"where these chemicals act."},{"time":203107,"text":"Otherwise, we're going to keep pouring oil all over our mental engines"},{"time":206586,"text":"and suffering the consequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209543,"text":"Now to begin to overcome our ignorance"},{"time":212602,"text":"of the role of brain chemistry in brain circuitry,"},{"time":216136,"text":"it's helpful to work on what we biologists call"},{"time":218816,"text":"\"model organisms,\""},{"time":220395,"text":"animals like fruit flies and laboratory mice,"},{"time":223729,"text":"in which we can apply powerful genetic techniques"},{"time":227154,"text":"to molecularly identify and pinpoint"},{"time":230779,"text":"specific classes of neurons,"},{"time":232342,"text":"as you heard about in Allan Jones's talk this morning."},{"time":235245,"text":"Moreover, once we can do that,"},{"time":237706,"text":"we can actually activate specific neurons"},{"time":240455,"text":"or we can destroy or inhibit the activity of those neurons."},{"time":244666,"text":"So if we inhibit a particular type of neuron,"},{"time":247380,"text":"and we find that a behavior is blocked,"},{"time":249845,"text":"we can conclude that those neurons"},{"time":252059,"text":"are necessary for that behavior."},{"time":255023,"text":"On the other hand, if we activate a group of neurons"},{"time":257405,"text":"and we find that that produces the behavior,"},{"time":260219,"text":"we can conclude that those neurons are sufficient for the behavior."},{"time":264293,"text":"So in this way, by doing this kind of test,"},{"time":267302,"text":"we can draw cause and effect relationships"},{"time":270825,"text":"between the activity of specific neurons"},{"time":273181,"text":"in particular circuits and particular behaviors,"},{"time":276094,"text":"something that is extremely difficult, if not impossible,"},{"time":278531,"text":"to do right now in humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283582,"text":"But can an organism like a fruit fly, which is --"},{"time":286419,"text":"it's a great model organism"},{"time":288619,"text":"because it's got a small brain,"},{"time":291157,"text":"it's capable of complex and sophisticated behaviors,"},{"time":294944,"text":"it breeds quickly, and it's cheap."},{"time":298094,"text":"But can an organism like this"},{"time":299889,"text":"teach us anything about emotion-like states?"},{"time":303732,"text":"Do these organisms even have emotion-like states,"},{"time":307032,"text":"or are they just little digital robots?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310395,"text":"Charles Darwin believed that insects have emotion"},{"time":313595,"text":"and express them in their behaviors, as he wrote"},{"time":316145,"text":"in his 1872 monograph on the expression of the emotions in man and animals."},{"time":321338,"text":"And my eponymous colleague, Seymour Benzer, believed it as well."},{"time":324857,"text":"Seymour is the man that introduced the use of drosophila"},{"time":328271,"text":"here at CalTech in the '60s as a model organism"},{"time":331794,"text":"to study the connection between genes and behavior."},{"time":335391,"text":"Seymour recruited me to CalTech in the late 1980s."},{"time":338998,"text":"He was my Jedi and my rabbi while he was here,"},{"time":343432,"text":"and Seymour taught me both to love flies"},{"time":345820,"text":"and also to play with science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348869,"text":"So how do we ask this question?"},{"time":351985,"text":"It's one thing to believe that flies have emotion-like states,"},{"time":356045,"text":"but how do we actually find out whether that's true or not?"},{"time":359208,"text":"Now, in humans we often infer emotional states,"},{"time":363158,"text":"as you'll hear later today, from facial expressions."},{"time":367063,"text":"However, it's a little difficult to do that in fruit flies."},{"time":370783,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":374096,"text":"It's kind of like landing on Mars"},{"time":377233,"text":"and looking out the window of your spaceship"},{"time":379938,"text":"at all the little green men who are surrounding it"},{"time":382408,"text":"and trying to figure out, \"How do I find out"},{"time":384814,"text":"if they have emotions or not?\""},{"time":387169,"text":"What can we do? It's not so easy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390712,"text":"Well, one of the ways that we can start"},{"time":392897,"text":"is to try to come up with some general characteristics"},{"time":397022,"text":"or properties of emotion-like states"},{"time":400770,"text":"such as arousal, and see if we can identify"},{"time":404234,"text":"any fly behaviors that might exhibit some of those properties."},{"time":409610,"text":"So three important ones that I can think of"},{"time":412430,"text":"are persistence, gradations in intensity, and valence."},{"time":417102,"text":"Persistence means long-lasting."},{"time":419436,"text":"We all know that the stimulus that triggers an emotion"},{"time":423397,"text":"causes that emotion to last long after the stimulus is gone."},{"time":428413,"text":"Gradations of intensity means what it sounds like."},{"time":431503,"text":"You can dial up the intensity or dial down the intensity of an emotion."},{"time":436086,"text":"If you're a little bit unhappy, the corners of your mouth"},{"time":438686,"text":"turn down and you sniffle,"},{"time":440373,"text":"and if you're very unhappy, tears pour down your face"},{"time":443511,"text":"and you might sob."},{"time":445343,"text":"Valence means good or bad, positive or negative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449722,"text":"So we decided to see if flies could be provoked into showing"},{"time":454174,"text":"the kind of behavior that you see"},{"time":456625,"text":"by the proverbial wasp at the picnic table,"},{"time":459435,"text":"you know, the one that keeps coming back to your hamburger"},{"time":462120,"text":"the more vigorously you try to swat it away,"},{"time":464649,"text":"and it seems to keep getting irritated."},{"time":466933,"text":"So we built a device, which we call a puff-o-mat,"},{"time":470580,"text":"in which we could deliver little brief air puffs to fruit flies"},{"time":474925,"text":"in these plastic tubes in our laboratory bench"},{"time":477701,"text":"and blow them away."},{"time":479426,"text":"And what we found is that if we gave these flies"},{"time":482665,"text":"in the puff-o-mat several puffs in a row,"},{"time":485513,"text":"they became somewhat hyperactive"},{"time":488202,"text":"and continued to run around for some time after the air puffs actually stopped"},{"time":492637,"text":"and took a while to calm down."},{"time":495501,"text":"So we quantified this behavior"},{"time":497690,"text":"using custom locomotor tracking software"},{"time":500702,"text":"developed with my collaborator Pietro Perona,"},{"time":503502,"text":"who's in the electrical engineering division here at CalTech."},{"time":507114,"text":"And what this quantification showed us is that,"},{"time":509928,"text":"upon experiencing a train of these air puffs,"},{"time":513152,"text":"the flies appear to enter a kind of state of hyperactivity"},{"time":517466,"text":"which is persistent, long-lasting,"},{"time":520064,"text":"and also appears to be graded."},{"time":522568,"text":"More puffs, or more intense puffs,"},{"time":525427,"text":"make the state last for a longer period of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529340,"text":"So now we wanted to try to understand something"},{"time":531376,"text":"about what controls the duration of this state."},{"time":535090,"text":"So we decided to use our puff-o-mat"},{"time":537941,"text":"and our automated tracking software"},{"time":539996,"text":"to screen through hundreds of lines of mutant fruit flies"},{"time":543778,"text":"to see if we could find any that showed abnormal responses to the air puffs."},{"time":548857,"text":"And this is one of the great things about fruit flies."},{"time":551204,"text":"There are repositories where you can just pick up the phone"},{"time":553997,"text":"and order hundreds of vials of flies of different mutants"},{"time":557638,"text":"and screen them in your assay and then find out"},{"time":559810,"text":"what gene is affected in the mutation."},{"time":563129,"text":"So doing the screen, we discovered one mutant"},{"time":566641,"text":"that took much longer than normal to calm down"},{"time":570115,"text":"after the air puffs,"},{"time":572392,"text":"and when we examined the gene that was affected in this mutation,"},{"time":576342,"text":"it turned out to encode a dopamine receptor."},{"time":579947,"text":"That's right -- flies, like people, have dopamine,"},{"time":582958,"text":"and it acts on their brains and on their synapses"},{"time":585730,"text":"through the same dopamine receptor molecules"},{"time":588280,"text":"that you and I have."},{"time":590669,"text":"Dopamine plays a number of important functions in the brain,"},{"time":594155,"text":"including in attention, arousal, reward,"},{"time":597268,"text":"and disorders of the dopamine system have been linked"},{"time":600681,"text":"to a number of mental disorders including drug abuse,"},{"time":603781,"text":"Parkinson's disease, and ADHD."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608015,"text":"Now, in genetics, it's a little counterintuitive."},{"time":610805,"text":"We tend to infer the normal function of something"},{"time":614065,"text":"by what doesn't happen when we take it away,"},{"time":617775,"text":"by the opposite of what we see when we take it away."},{"time":620778,"text":"So when we take away the dopamine receptor"},{"time":623791,"text":"and the flies take longer to calm down,"},{"time":626348,"text":"from that we infer that the normal function of this receptor and dopamine"},{"time":630194,"text":"is to cause the flies to calm down faster after the puff."},{"time":634679,"text":"And that's a bit reminiscent of ADHD,"},{"time":637629,"text":"which has been linked to disorders of the dopamine system in humans."},{"time":641604,"text":"Indeed, if we increase the levels of dopamine in normal flies"},{"time":646210,"text":"by feeding them cocaine"},{"time":647920,"text":"after getting the appropriate DEA license"},{"time":650892,"text":"— oh my God -- (Laughter) —"},{"time":654892,"text":"we find indeed that these cocaine-fed flies"},{"time":658064,"text":"calm down faster than normal flies do,"},{"time":661106,"text":"and that's also reminiscent of ADHD,"},{"time":664305,"text":"which is often treated with drugs like Ritalin"},{"time":666350,"text":"that act similarly to cocaine."},{"time":669369,"text":"So slowly I began to realize that what started out"},{"time":672518,"text":"as a rather playful attempt to try to annoy fruit flies"},{"time":676167,"text":"might actually have some relevance to a human psychiatric disorder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680143,"text":"Now, how far does this analogy go?"},{"time":682369,"text":"As many of you know, individuals afflicted with ADHD"},{"time":685491,"text":"also have learning disabilities."},{"time":687828,"text":"Is that true of our dopamine receptor mutant flies?"},{"time":691394,"text":"Remarkably, the answer is yes."},{"time":694114,"text":"As Seymour showed back in the 1970s,"},{"time":696742,"text":"flies, like songbirds, as you just heard,"},{"time":699193,"text":"are capable of learning."},{"time":700926,"text":"You can train a fly to avoid an odor, shown here in blue,"},{"time":705369,"text":"if you pair that odor with a shock."},{"time":707757,"text":"Then when you give those trained flies the chance to choose"},{"time":711141,"text":"between a tube with the shock-paired odor and another odor,"},{"time":714295,"text":"it avoids the tube containing the blue odor that was paired with shock."},{"time":718495,"text":"Well, if you do this test on dopamine receptor mutant flies,"},{"time":721997,"text":"they don't learn. Their learning score is zero."},{"time":724462,"text":"They flunk out of CalTech."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728273,"text":"So that means that these flies have two abnormalities,"},{"time":733021,"text":"or phenotypes, as we geneticists call them,"},{"time":736071,"text":"that one finds in ADHD: hyperactivity and learning disability."},{"time":741583,"text":"Now what's the causal relationship, if anything, between these phenotypes?"},{"time":745946,"text":"In ADHD, it's often assumed that the hyperactivity"},{"time":749859,"text":"causes the learning disability."},{"time":751765,"text":"The kids can't sit still long enough to focus, so they don't learn."},{"time":755484,"text":"But it could equally be the case that it's the learning disabilities"},{"time":758780,"text":"that cause the hyperactivity."},{"time":760652,"text":"Because the kids can't learn, they look for other things to distract their attention."},{"time":765122,"text":"And a final possibility is that there's no relationship at all"},{"time":768179,"text":"between learning disabilities and hyperactivity,"},{"time":770583,"text":"but that they are caused by a common underlying mechanism in ADHD."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775498,"text":"Now people have been wondering about this for a long time"},{"time":777840,"text":"in humans, but in flies we can actually test this."},{"time":781328,"text":"And the way that we do this is to delve deeply into the mind"},{"time":784412,"text":"of the fly and begin to untangle its circuitry using genetics."},{"time":788678,"text":"We take our dopamine receptor mutant flies"},{"time":791140,"text":"and we genetically restore, or cure, the dopamine receptor"},{"time":795704,"text":"by putting a good copy of the dopamine receptor gene"},{"time":798939,"text":"back into the fly brain."},{"time":800990,"text":"But in each fly, we put it back only into certain neurons"},{"time":804825,"text":"and not in others, and then we test each of these flies"},{"time":808539,"text":"for their ability to learn and for hyperactivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812207,"text":"Remarkably, we find we can completely dissociate these two abnormalities."},{"time":817025,"text":"If we put a good copy of the dopamine receptor back"},{"time":819688,"text":"in this elliptical structure called the central complex,"},{"time":822649,"text":"the flies are no longer hyperactive, but they still can't learn."},{"time":826726,"text":"On the other hand, if we put the receptor back in a different structure"},{"time":829452,"text":"called the mushroom body,"},{"time":830970,"text":"the learning deficit is rescued, the flies learn well,"},{"time":834055,"text":"but they're still hyperactive."},{"time":835885,"text":"What that tells us is that dopamine"},{"time":838135,"text":"is not bathing the brain of these flies like soup."},{"time":841527,"text":"Rather, it's acting to control two different functions"},{"time":844689,"text":"on two different circuits,"},{"time":846323,"text":"so the reason there are two things wrong with our dopamine receptor flies"},{"time":850227,"text":"is that the same receptor is controlling two different functions"},{"time":854402,"text":"in two different regions of the brain."},{"time":857265,"text":"Whether the same thing is true in ADHD in humans"},{"time":860327,"text":"we don't know, but these kinds of results"},{"time":862703,"text":"should at least cause us to consider that possibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866180,"text":"So these results make me and my colleagues more convinced than ever"},{"time":870153,"text":"that the brain is not a bag of chemical soup,"},{"time":873565,"text":"and it's a mistake to try to treat complex psychiatric disorders"},{"time":877092,"text":"just by changing the flavor of the soup."},{"time":879803,"text":"What we need to do is to use our ingenuity and our scientific knowledge"},{"time":884020,"text":"to try to design a new generation of treatments"},{"time":886728,"text":"that are targeted to specific neurons and specific regions of the brain"},{"time":891016,"text":"that are affected in particular psychiatric disorders."},{"time":894354,"text":"If we can do that, we may be able to cure these disorders"},{"time":897554,"text":"without the unpleasant side effects,"},{"time":899601,"text":"putting the oil back in our mental engines,"},{"time":902347,"text":"just where it's needed. Thank you very much."}]}]}